<style>


    .home_body {
        background-image: url("https://wiki.nytolia.net/~gitbook/ogimage/jpVroBMZeJYmHIFDVjwv");
        height: auto;
        min-height: 45vh;
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: center;
        width: 95.7%;
        padding: 3rem 2rem;
        color: #555;
        font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
    }

        .home_body h1 {
            color: #3b82f6;
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .home_body p {
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.7;
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: auto;
            color: #e2e2e2;
        }

    /* Features Section */
    .features {
        width: 90%;
        margin: 5rem auto 2rem auto;
        text-align: center;
    }

        .features h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            color: #111827;
        }

        .features p {
            color: #555;
            font-size: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

    .row {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-around;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    .features_column {
        flex: 1 1 45%;
        background: #e6f2ff;
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        text-align: left;
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 1.2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    }

        .features_column img {
            height: 100px;
            border-radius: 20%;
            object-fit: cover;
        }

        .features_column p {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: #333;
            line-height: 1.5;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .features_column button {
            padding: 8px 16px;
            background-color: #111827;
            border: none;
            color: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

            .features_column button:hover {
                background-color: #004ccc;
            }
    /* Footer */
    .footer {
        width: 95.6%;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 2rem;
        background-color: #0d1b2a;
        color: white;
        margin-top: 5rem;
    }

        .footer h3 {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .footer p {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto 1.5rem auto;
            color: #dbe2ef;
        }

        .footer .icons i {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            margin: 0 10px;
            color: #3f88c5;
            transition: transform 0.3s, color 0.3s;
        }

            .footer .icons i:hover {
                transform: scale(1.2);
                color: #90e0ef;
            }

</style>

<!-- Home Section -->
<div class="home_body">
    <h1>Welcome to the Contract Monthly Claim System <strong><em>(CMCS)</em></strong></h1>
    <p>
        The Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS) is a digital platform designed to simplify and improve how academic claims are submitted, reviewed, and finalized within an institution.
        Traditionally, these claims are handled through manual or partly digital processes, often resulting in delays, lost paperwork, and lack of transparency.
        CMCS addresses these challenges by providing a secure and user-friendly online system where lecturers can register, log in, and submit claims with all necessary details.
        Programme coordinators can review, approve or reject claims, while programme management finalizes decisions. This structured workflow ensures accountability and transparency at every step.
    </p>
</div>

<!-- Features -->
<div class="features">
    <h1>What Are Some Of Our Features</h1>
    <p>Our features are simple, efficient, and easy to use.</p>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="features_column">
            <img src="https://media1.tenor.com/m/1vwVyZbs2JIAAAAC/claimnow.gif" alt="Submit Claim" />
            <div>
                <p>
                    The Submit Claim feature allows lecturers to easily submit their academic claims through a secure and user-friendly form.
                    Lecturers can provide details like sessions, hours, rates, and upload supporting documents. Claims are recorded with submission dates and set to a "Pending" status for processing.
                </p>
                <a href="@Url.Action("SubmitClaim", "Home")">
                    <button><i class="fa fa-paper-plane"></i> Submit Claim</button>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="features_column">
            <img src="https://data.textstudio.com/output/sample/animated/7/3/1/5/claim-8-5137.gif" alt="Track Claim" />
            <div>
                <p>
                    The Track Claim feature gives lecturers a full view of their submitted claims, including statuses like Pending, Approved, Rejected, or Finalized.
                    Claims are displayed with key details and real-time updates, ensuring transparency throughout the approval process.
                </p>
                <a href="@Url.Action("TrackClaim", "Home")">
                    <button><i class="fa fa-line-chart"></i> Track Claim</button>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

